channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Agrees to Debate Kamala Harris—but on His Terms
Trump agrees to debate Kamala Harris on Fox News
item.description: Former President Trump said he has agreed to a debate on Fox News against Vice President Kamala Harris in Pennsylvania after she became the Democratic Party's presidential nominee.

item.title: Shapiro Walks Back Criticisms of Palestinian Terrorists
item.description: Pennsylvania Gov. Josh Shapiro has come under scrutiny for an opinion piece he wrote 30 years ago, now that the Democrat is a top contender to be Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate, The Philadelphia Inquirer reported Friday.

item.title: STUNNING: Ninth Circuit Reverses Its Ruling on Voter Registration and Proof of Citizenship in Arizona
GOP senators react to acting Secret Service Director Rowe’s press conference: 'Clearly a cover-up’
item.description: Republicans react to acting USSS Director Rowe's press conference Friday, where he gave updates on the investigation into the assassination attempt on former President Trump.

item.title: Gov. Abbott Sets Nov. 5 Special Election for Jackson Lee Seat
item.description: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott has set a special election for Nov. 5 to fill the vacant seat of the late Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee, coinciding with the general election, The Hill reported Friday.

item.title: 'Gut Wrenching': Family of Marc Fogel, Who Biden 'Left Behind' in Russia, Blasts Prisoner Swap Deal
Kyle Rittenhouse walks back declaring he was not voting for Trump for not being 'pro-gun enough'
item.description: Following intense backlash from his comments post on X, Kyle Rittenhouse backtracks on saying that he won't vote for former president Donald Trump.

item.title: UAW Chief: Trump Has 'Never Supported' Working Class
item.description: The Head of the United Auto Workers said former President Donald Trump has "never supported working-class people" and is beholden to billionaires. In an interview on Friday, Shawn Fain said Trump has never supported unions, "but he sure as ...

item.title: Oil Giant Chevron Says Adios to CA After 145 Years, TX Gov. Abbott Invites Them to 'Drill Baby Drill'
Philadelphia mayor's social media video sparks speculation of leaked Kamala Harris running mate
item.description: A post from Philadelphia's mayor seemed to suggest Gov. Josh Shapiro might be Kamala Harris' chosen running mate.

item.title: GOP Senators Urge Biden to End Partial Israel Arms Embargo
item.description: As tension in the Middle East mounts, Republican senators are calling on President Joe Biden to end his partial arms embargo against Israel.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: CA Fire Search and Rescue Saves a Dog and Her Puppies and a Rainbow Bridge Farewell
Butler rally was the first event Secret Service deployed counter snipers to Trump detail: acting director
item.description: Acting Secret Service Director Ronald Rowe Jr. revealed the Butler rally was the first event where Secret Service counter snipers were deployed to former President Trump's detail.

item.title: Missouri AG Bailey to Newsmax: Harris Flew Illegal Migrants Into State
item.description: Missouri Attorney General Andrew Bailey told Newsmax on Friday that Missourians have a right "to know how many illegal aliens border czar Kamala Harris transported illegally into our state" under the now shuttered humanitarian parole program.
